First you need to take the @flank steak{2} out of your fridge to bring it up to room temperature. Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and boil @water{150%ml} for later. Chop the @new potatoes{1} into small 2cm cubes. Lightly crush the @black peppercorns{3/4%tsp} in a #pestle & mortar{}.

> Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar put the peppercorns between two sheets of foil/clingfilm and give them a little whack with a rolling pin.

Remove the @rosemary{2} leaves from their stalks and very finely chop. Put the potatoes on a #baking tray{}, sprinkle over the chopped rosemary leaves and drizzle over 1 1/2 tbsp of @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}. Sprinkle over @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Give the baking tray a good shake so the potatoes are evenly coated and cook on the top shelf of your oven for ~{30%minutes} until crispy (shake occasionally).

Peel and very finely chop the @echalion shallot{1/2} and cut the @broccoli{1} into florets.

Put your broccoli florets on a baking tray, add @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of pepper and pop in your oven for ~{15%minutes} until slightly crispy.

Once your steak has come to room temperature, season it with a @salt{pinch}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with @oil{1%tbsp}. Once almost smoking hot, lay the steak into the pan and press it down.

> Tip: Lay the steak away from your body to stop oil spitting at you.

Cook for ~{3%minutes} each side for medium. Only turn the steak once and rest on a warm #plate{} once cooked.

> Tip: Cook for a little longer if you like your steak well done.

Once the steak is removed from the pan, turn the heat to medium-low and add @olive oil{2%tsp} to the pan along with the shallot. After cooking for ~{2%minutes}, add the peppercorns. One minute later, add the 150ml of boiled water and stir in the @beef stock pot{1/2}.

Bubble away for a few mins and once your sauce has reduced by half, take off the heat and stir in the @creme fraiche{3/4%tsp}.

> Tip: For a decadent touch, add 1 tsp of butter at this point (if you have any).

Slice your steak diagonally into 1cm strips and serve everything together with your homemade peppercorn sauce.